# Smart Classroom Web Dashboard

A real-time web dashboard for the Bio-Glove smart classroom system. Two user roles — **Teacher** and **Student** — each with distinct views. The dashboard reads from Firebase Realtime Database and uses the browser's Web Speech API (or Whisper API) for speech-to-text transcription.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Whisper Integration**: The user mentioned "what teacher speaks must be sent to student transcribed with whisper." Since Whisper typically runs server-side (python), I'll use the **browser's built-in Web Speech API** (`webkitSpeechRecognition`) for real-time speech-to-text on the teacher's browser, then push the transcript to Firebase so the student can see it. This avoids needing a backend server. If you specifically need OpenAI Whisper instead, let me know and we'll add a Python backend.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Sign Language Data**: You mentioned signs will be stored at `sign/s01/`. The current [unified_monitor.py](file:///home/minindu/Documents/bio-glove/ml/unified_monitor.py) doesn't push sign predictions to Firebase yet. I'll build the dashboard to **listen on `sign/{studentId}/`** — you'll need to add a Firebase push in [unified_monitor.py](file:///home/minindu/Documents/bio-glove/ml/unified_monitor.py) (a one-liner: `db.reference(f"sign/{STUDENT_ID}").set({"label": sign_label, "confidence": sign_confidence})`) to make it work end-to-end. I can add that too if you'd like.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Environment Data**: You said `environment/s01/ac:` and `environment/s01/lighting:` — the dashboard will listen on this path. You'll manually add this data to Firebase later.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Student Camera View**: The student needs to see their own camera feed. This will be done entirely in-browser using `getUserMedia()` — no data is sent anywhere, it's just a local mirror view with no ML annotations.

## Proposed Changes

### Web Dashboard (Vite + Vanilla JS)

All files will be created inside `/home/minindu/Documents/bio-glove/web-dashboard/`.

---

#### [NEW] `web-dashboard/` — Vite project

Initialize with `npx -y create-vite@latest ./ --template vanilla`.

---

#### [NEW] [index.html](file:///home/minindu/Documents/bio-glove/web-dashboard/index.html)

Entry point. Contains the login/role selection screen and both dashboard views (toggled by JS). Single-page app approach — no router needed.

---

#### [NEW] [style.css](file:///home/minindu/Documents/bio-glove/web-dashboard/style.css)

Complete design system:
- Dark mode with deep navy/charcoal palette
- Glassmorphism cards for data panels
- Vibrant accent colors (emerald green for engaged, red for alerts)
- Inter font from Google Fonts
- Smooth transitions and micro-animations
- Responsive grid layout

---

#### [NEW] [main.js](file:///home/minindu/Documents/bio-glove/web-dashboard/main.js)

Application logic:
- **Role selection**: Login screen with Teacher/Student toggle and student ID selector
- **Firebase initialization**: Connect to `smart-classroom-981e2-default-rtdb`
- **Teacher Dashboard**:
  - Student selector dropdown (s01–s05)
  - Real-time listener on `engagement/{sid}` → engagement status
  - Real-time listener on `sign/{sid}` → detected sign display
  - Real-time listener on `environment/{sid}` → AC & lighting
  - Web Speech API for mic capture → transcription pushed to `transcription/{sid}`
- **Student Dashboard**:
  - Local camera feed via `getUserMedia()`
  - Real-time listener on `transcription/{sid}` → shows what teacher said
  - Sign detection status indicator (reads `sign/{sid}`)

---

#### [NEW] [firebase-config.js](file:///home/minindu/Documents/bio-glove/web-dashboard/firebase-config.js)

Firebase Web SDK configuration:
```js
const firebaseConfig = {
  databaseURL: "https://smart-classroom-981e2-default-rtdb.asia-southeast1.firebasedatabase.app"
};
```
Uses Firebase Realtime Database CDN (compat v9 modular SDK).

---

### ML Script Update (Optional)

#### [MODIFY] [unified_monitor.py](file:///home/minindu/Documents/bio-glove/ml/unified_monitor.py)

Add one Firebase push for sign detection results to `sign/{STUDENT_ID}/`:
```python
sign_ref = db.reference(f"sign/{STUDENT_ID}")
# Inside run_sign_inference, after updating sign_label:
sign_ref.set({"label": sign_label, "confidence": float(sign_confidence)})
```

## Firebase Database Structure

| Path | Data | Producer | Consumer |
|------|------|----------|----------|
| `engagement/{sid}/` | `engagement_score`, `engagement_status` | [unified_monitor.py](file:///home/minindu/Documents/bio-glove/ml/unified_monitor.py) | Teacher dashboard |
| `sign/{sid}/` | `label`, `confidence` | [unified_monitor.py](file:///home/minindu/Documents/bio-glove/ml/unified_monitor.py) (to be added) | Teacher dashboard |
| `environment/{sid}/` | [ac](file:///home/minindu/Documents/bio-glove/ml/unified_monitor.py#498-527), `lighting` | Manual / IoT (later) | Teacher dashboard |
| `transcription/{sid}/` | [text](file:///home/minindu/Documents/bio-glove/ml/advanced_engagement.py#137-141), `timestamp` | Teacher dashboard (Web Speech API) | Student dashboard |
| `emotion/{sid}/` | `stress_score`, `emotion_label` | [unified_monitor.py](file:///home/minindu/Documents/bio-glove/ml/unified_monitor.py) | Teacher dashboard |

## Verification Plan

### Browser Testing
1. Run `npm run dev` in `web-dashboard/`
2. Open the browser to the dev server URL
3. Verify login screen renders with role selection
4. Select **Teacher** role → verify teacher dashboard loads with student selector
5. Select **Student** role → verify student dashboard loads with camera feed  
6. Check that Firebase listeners are active (engagement, sign, environment panels update when data is present in Firebase)

### Manual Verification
- **Teacher mic transcription**: Click "Start Speaking" → speak → verify text appears and is pushed to Firebase `transcription/{sid}/`
- **Student transcript display**: Open student dashboard in a second tab → verify teacher's transcription appears in real-time
- **Environment data**: Manually write `{ac: "ON", lighting: "Bright"}` to `environment/s01/` in Firebase console → verify it appears on teacher dashboard
